# Prefer "task" over "job"

In this codebase, **always use "task"** (not "job") when naming or referring to a single unit of queued work.

## API and code

- **Methods**: `onTaskFinished`, not `onJobFinished`.
- **Payloads**: Use `taskId`, not `jobId`, in callback payloads and public types.
- **Variables**: Prefer `task`, `taskId`, `taskIds` over `job`, `jobId`, `jobIds` in user-facing code and examples.

## Examples

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
remq.onTaskFinished((task) => {
  console.log('Task finished:', task.taskId, task.status);
});

// ❌ BAD
remq.onJobFinished((job) => {
  console.log('Job finished:', job.jobId);
});
```

Internal implementation (e.g. Redis keys, stream keys) may still use "job" where it predates this convention; when adding new APIs, docs, or examples, use **task** first.
